# =============================================================================
# deploy/prod/.env.example
# Host-side environment for the shamanktmweb production deploy.
#
# This file exists for parity with the projectX deploy layout. The website
# itself is a static export — all NEXT_PUBLIC_* values are baked into the
# Docker image at build time, NOT read at runtime. Set those as GitHub
# Actions repo variables/secrets so the CI build picks them up:
#
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_MODE          (vars)    — live | coming-soon
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_PROJECTX_API_BASE  (vars)    — public API base URL
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_PROJECTX_API_KEY   (secrets) — public API key (origin-pinned)
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_PROJECTX_ORIGIN    (vars)    — origin pin, e.g. https://shamankathmandu.com
#   PROJECTX_API_MODE              (vars)    — mock | live
#   DOCKERHUB_USERNAME             (secrets) — used by GitHub Actions login
#   DOCKERHUB_TOKEN                (secrets) — used by GitHub Actions login
#
# Copy this file to .env on the EC2 host (./setup.sh does this for you).
# Currently no host-side runtime variables are required.
# =============================================================================
